To fix the error related to vkUpdateDescriptorSets, you need to ensure that the descriptor set is not in use by any command buffer when you attempt to update it. One way to achieve this is by using the VK_DESCRIPTOR_BINDING_UPDATE_AFTER_BIND_BIT_EXT flag when creating the descriptor set layout. This allows descriptor sets to be updated even if they are in use by a command buffer. Here's how you can modify the code:

1. Modify the descriptor set layout creation to include the VK_DESCRIPTOR_BINDING_UPDATE_AFTER_BIND_BIT_EXT flag:

```cpp
VkDescriptorSetLayoutBinding layoutBinding = {};
layoutBinding.binding = 0;
layoutBinding.descriptorType = VK_DESCRIPTOR_TYPE_UNIFORM_BUFFER;
layoutBinding.descriptorCount = 1;
layoutBinding.stageFlags = VK_SHADER_STAGE_VERTEX_BIT;
layoutBinding.pImmutableSamplers = nullptr;
layoutBinding.flags = VK_DESCRIPTOR_BINDING_UPDATE_AFTER_BIND_BIT_EXT;
```

2. Ensure that the descriptor pool is created with the VK_DESCRIPTOR_POOL_CREATE_UPDATE_AFTER_BIND_BIT_EXT flag:

```cpp
VkDescriptorPoolCreateInfo poolInfo = {};
poolInfo.sType = VK_STRUCTURE_TYPE_DESCRIPTOR_POOL_CREATE_INFO;
poolInfo.flags = VK_DESCRIPTOR_POOL_CREATE_UPDATE_AFTER_BIND_BIT_EXT;
// Other poolInfo settings...
```

3. Recreate the descriptor sets with the updated layout and pool settings.

By making these changes, you allow the descriptor sets to be updated even when they are in use, thus resolving the validation error.

