output:
 The issue you're encountering is due to trying to update a descriptor set layout that is currently being used by a command buffer. To fix this issue, you should either create a new descriptor set layout that isn't currently being used or wait for the command buffer to finish executing before updating the descriptor set layout.

In your code, you have the following line in the `GameObject::Render()` function:
```c++
material->UpdateBufferBinding(descriptorSet, mvpBuffer, device, sizeof(MVP));
```
This line is trying to update the descriptor set layout of the material, which is causing the validation error. To fix this issue, you can move this line to a different part of your code, for example, in the `GameObject::Update()` function, where it's not being used by a command buffer.

Another solution is to create a new descriptor set layout specifically for the mvpBuffer and use that instead of trying to update the existing one. You can add a new function to the `Material` class that creates a new descriptor set layout for the mvpBuffer and returns it. Then, in the `GameObject::Render()` function, you can use this new descriptor set layout instead of trying to update the existing one.

Here's an example of how you can modify the `Material` class to create a new descriptor set layout for the mvpBuffer:
```c++
class Material {
public:
    // ...
    VkDescriptorSet CreateMVPDescriptorSet(VkDevice device, VkDescriptorPool descriptorPool, VkDescriptorSetLayout layout);
private:
    // ...
    VkDescriptorSet mvpDescriptorSet;
};

VkDescriptorSet Material::CreateMVPDescriptorSet(VkDevice device, VkDescriptorPool descriptorPool, VkDescriptorSetLayout layout) {
    VkDescriptorSetAllocateInfo allocInfo = {};
    allocInfo.sType = VK_STRUCTURE_TYPE_DESCRIPTOR_SET_ALLOCATE_INFO;
    allocInfo.descriptorPool = descriptorPool;
    allocInfo.descriptorSetCount = 1;
    allocInfo.pSetLayouts = &layout;

    VkDescriptorSet descriptorSet;
    if (vkAllocateDescriptorSets(device, &allocInfo, &descriptorSet) != VK_SUCCESS) {
        throw std::runtime_error("Failed to allocate descriptor set for mvpBuffer!");
    }

    mvpDescriptorSet = descriptorSet;
    return descriptorSet;
}
```
